title: For Sale/Trade:  Trijicon Dual Illuminated RMR
postcontent:
This is a barely used Trijicon RMR08-A. This series RMR requires no batteries, because it utilizes tritium and fiber optics to illuminate the reticle. The reticle is an amber triangle. This is far superior to a dot because you use the apex of the triangle as your point of aim rather than the center of a dot. The smallest dot Trijicon offers in this model is 7 MOA, that means it covers 7 inches at 100 yards, 14 inches at 200yds, 21 inches at 300, etc...  You put the triangle at the top of center mass and you have a "kill shot" from 0-300yds. 

The base that comes with this RMR is the Trijicon low profile picatinny mount. I still have the original Trijicon carrying case and all the paperwork. The price is firm. Try finding a better price anywhere.
